        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 7 at 1:47PM EDT by NWS Louisville KY</headline>
        <description>At 146 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Highlands, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lexington, Cardinal Hill, Bryan Station, Meadowthorpe, Dunbar High
School, Northland, Highlands, U K Arboretum, Thoroughbred Acres, and
Chevy Chase.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
